xlaunch
*******

xlaunch is a simple Windows GUI tool for starting the XWin X server for Windows.


building
========

'./configure; make; make install' should configure, build, and install xlaunch

g++, libX11, libxml-2.0 are required to build xlaunch.

In addition, the "Microsoft HTML Help Workshop 1.3" is required for the CHM compiler hhc.exe.
It can be downloaded from [1].

[1] http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms669985

'configure' accepts the '--with-htmlhelp-path' option to specify the location of the HtmlHelp
SDK, which defaults to /cygdrive/c/Program Files/HTML Help Workshop/
